Reserve Bank governor Lesetja Kganyago today announced a drop in the repo-rate down to 6.75% with Prime lending rate at 10.25%.The Monetary Policy Committee elected to reduce the repo rate by 25 basis points.Today&#8217;s announcement comes after some analysts had speculated that the repo rate would be retained at 7%.The last time the MPC met was on May 23-25, just after Stats SA announced that the country has slipped into a technical recession.In its last MPC statement in May, Reserve Bank governor Lesetja Kganyago said the committee remained of the view that the current level of the repo rate at 7% was appropriate and that the MPC was likely at the end of the tightening cycle.-TNA Reporter